Title: ROVER SURVIVOR
Description:
Rover Survivor is the latest addition to the Survivor series, this will be the first ever Survivor event for the Rover Section.
Rover Survivor is set up to be a team (two person) event, working together to perform various tasks under challenging scenarios. It allows you, under controlled conditions, to see if you have what it takes to make it with minimal gear in a survival scenario and have the ability to make the right decisions in stressful situations.
With your Teammate you can learn more, remember more and achieve more.
Rover Survivor is a team event but don’t worry if you’re ‘flying solo’, just sign up and we will pair you up with another ‘lone wolf’.

Title: County Commissioner Governance Briefing
Description:
Governance Briefing for County Commissioners.

At the last County Commissioners Conference in January, the Governance Review Group (GRG) gave an outline of proposals to restructure Scouting Ireland at a National level and has since been working on these in more detail.  We committed at that time to briefing County Commissioners on the final proposals prior to launching them to the membership at large.

National Council will meet again at the end of June to consider notice of motion to give effect to these proposals.

The Governance Review Group would like to invite County Commissioners and members of the National Management Committee to a joint briefing to be held on Sunday 20th May 2018 in Willington Scout Den, Templeogue, Dublin 6W.  The meeting will start at 10 a.m. and conclude no later than 1 p.m., a light lunch will be available afterwards.  This meeting is a single item agenda meeting to consider the proposals but is not the summer County Commissioners Conference, as this will now be held at a later date.

Title: Mountain Moot 2018
Description:
The weekend will offer a combination of training and skills development workshops, skills master
classes, old fashioned hiking and good camaraderie against the wonderful backdrop of the Wicklow Mountains.

Title: Scouting Ireland Assembly
Description:
You are invited to contribute to the future of Scouting Ireland at the Scouting Ireland Assembly in the Tullamore Court Hotel on Saturday 16th November. 

Participants will have the opportunity to:
1.	Receive updates on the work already done to reform Scouting Ireland’s structures to provide a modern, forward-looking organisational structure
2.	Take part in ‘beta testing’ of new programme ideas and techniques
3.	Participate in a question-and-answer session with the Board of Scouting Ireland.

The event begins at 11am on Saturday 16th November.

Title: Mountain Skills Training
Description: The Mountain Skills (MS) training course provides a general introduction to hillwalking in Ireland and the basics of mountain navigation. Offering a solid foundation for gaining personal mountaineering proficiency, Mountain Skills training teaches the necessary skills in mountain safety, navigation techniques, knowledge of hazards, and personal equipment, so that a person finishing the course may be in a position to safely, and competently, take to the hills. Mountain Skills training and assessment also provide foundation training for those who wish to progress to further leadership qualifications, such as the Mountain Leader (ML). Scouting Ireland offers this course, using Mountaineering Ireland approved course leaders, at greatly reduced cost to Scouters.

Title: Rover Survivor
Description:
ROVER SURVIVOR 2022

“THE ISLAND”

 

The world is in peril, as it emerges from a global pandemic it now faces the threat of nuclear war . 

As part of a government experiment a group of young scientists and adventures are dispatched to a top secret Island. 

The Challenge , to learn how to survive should the nightmare scenario become reality .

 You must learn to cope with various challenges,  using basic equipment you must survive,  you must learn how to sustain life should Ireland experience a nuclear attack. 

Have you the skills ? 

Can you work as part of a team ? 

Can you test yourself under stressful conditions ? 

Have you got what it takes to survive ......THE ISLAND!!!!!

Title: Explorer Belt 2022 (participants and support team)
Description: The Scouting Ireland Explorer Belt is the challenge of a lifetime; a chance to undertake an international expedition over ten days that brings a real understanding of a different country, its people and way of life. It is designed to help Rover Scouts develop this understanding of another country by travelling through that country, working as a small team to complete a series of projects, and, most importantly, by meeting local people. The event is for teams of two. Participants can sign up as a team or as an individual and every effort will be made to find you a partner.

Title: aa Mountain Havoc 23-25 September 2022
Description:
Be aware - a booking is only a confirmed booking when payment is made. It is suggested that payment is made when booking. If a payment is not made, it is not confirmed and another group can be assigned your places.

The Venture Scout Mountain Havoc is an event designed for Venture Scouts in Ireland. This event has been created to encourage more venture scouts to get out on the hills, to Develop their skills and abilities in this area and their appreciation for the Irish country side and further afield, to working as part of a team and getting to know other venture scouts from all over Ireland and learn what they are doing in their venture crews. The event is open to all venture scouts as long as they are reasonably fit and have adequate group & personal equipment. The event is a standing camp with facilities and there are 3 routes that participants can choice from prior to the event. These routes vary in length and difficulty and a route should be selected that suits the ability of the team

Offering a solid foundation for gaining personal mountaineering proficiency, Mountain Skills training teaches the necessary skills in mountain safety, navigation techniques, knowledge of hazards, and personal equipment, so that a person finishing the course may be in a position to safely, and competently, take to the hills. Mountain Skills training and assessment also provide foundation training for those who wish to progress to further leadership qualifications, such as the Mountain Leader (ML). 
Scouting Ireland offers this course, using Mountaineering Ireland approved course leaders, at greatly reduced cost to Scouters.

Title: Rover Survivor - Zombie Island - October 2020
Description:
Zombie Island - Rover Survivor Oct '22
Basic information 

The event is open to Rovers and Rover/scouters as indicated on SI profile page. It is not open to Scouters who are not also Rovers.

A booking is not confirmed unless the event fee is paid in full. Places can and will be offered to others if payment is not received.

Basic information and programme theme.

The World is not what it once was. The Dead now walk the land, while the living fight to survive to see the morning sun of tomorrow. The never-ending nightmare began and spread itself everywhere like a virus before civilization could react. The once thriving world full of dreams and prosperity now smells like pungent death. Life for the survivors is constantly being threatened by the dangers that await. In a world where humans are the prey, the survivors must acquire extraordinary skills in order to make it through just one more day.  
Are you brave or crazy enough to take on a challenge where every decision you make could be the difference between life and the undead? This challenge is not for the faint hearted, you will have to undertake your journey with the minimum of equipment and resources. Teams of Rover Scouts must work together to build shelters, light fires, scavenge resources, fight off the undead and any other obstacles they come across.

Title: Rover Survivor - Three Days In Hell
Description:
All that stands between you and a coveted place in the “Reconnaissance & Ordnance Volunteer Elite Reserves” is final selection. 

Nicknamed ‘Three Days in Hell’ by previous Survivors. This challenge will test physical endurance, mental toughness, pain and cold tolerance, teamwork, attitude, and your ability to perform work under high physical and mental stress, and sleep deprivation. Above all, it tests determination and desire. If you make it to the end, it will probably be the greatest achievement of your life, and with it comes the realization that you can do 20 X more than you ever thought possible. 

It is a defining moment that you will reach back to when in combat. You know that you will never, ever quit, or let a teammate down.

Do you think you're tough enough to complete this challenge?

Description:
The Crean Challenge Expedition is an annual event based on the experiences of Irish explorer Tom
Crean.

It aims to promote teamwork in patrols, to achieve a common
goal, and to personally challenge everyone to identify and achieve personal goals.

will be trained to the highest standards to ensure that they can achieve the expedition requirements.

This expedition will introduce participants to new cultures and experiences,

Title: Ceiliúradh
Description:
Ceiliúradh is the final step in the Rover Service project cycle. It is all about celebrating the work carried out by rover crews within their section, group and wider community. It gives rover crews the chance to share their experience from their service project as well as connect with other crews, all the while inspiring others to take on service projects of their own. This Ceiliúradh will be a special one as there has not been an event such as this for rovers since before the Covid-19 pandemic. Due to this, there have been 4 years of projects that have not been celebrated. To make this a memorable celebration of all the work carried out by rovers our theme is "A night at the Roscars"(Rover Oscars). Rovers, their Advisors and Group leaders will be able to nominate individuals and crews to receive a Roscars. This could be for exceptional service within a rover section, a completed rover service project or an award for special recognition.

The event will take place in a formal setting with attendees encouraged to dress formally. A meal will be served following the awards ceremony. The award ceremony will then take place. Following the awards ceremony there will be a dance. 

Any questions on this event please contact roverscouts@scouts.ie
Any questions about the booking please contact events@scouts.ie

Please note that all youth members will be expected to complete Safe from Harm training module 1 (SfH 1: Safe from Harm Essential Learnings) and submit proof of completion to the National Rover team. The module may be found at: https://learn.scout.org/resource/sfh-1-safe-harm-essential-learnings.

Online payments only:

Title: PEAK 2025
LocationTitle: Gartan Outdoor Education Centre, Church Hill Co. Donegal F92 T853
Description:
PEAK is a week long training adventure for Scouts and Ventures run over Easter week (18th April to 25th April 2025) in Gartan Outdoor Education Centre in Donegal.
For any Scout / Venture between the ages of 14 and 17 with hiking experience who wishes to be challenged, this is a unique opportunity. It is an intense roller coaster of a week; from Good Friday to the following Friday, participants are immersed in a week of challenge and adventure with an emphasis on navigation and expedition training.

The week culminates in a multiday expedition in the heart of the Donegal mountains, with participants completing a 30km wild country hike carrying all of the required equipment on their backs. Every other aspect of the week has been builds towards this: team building, leadership, navigation, orienteering, initiative exercises, route planning, mountain skills …

PEAK builds on Sionnach / MPC adventures and offers an additional challenge and trill for potential leaders of the future.

Teamwork, self-reliance, problem solving, a spectacular setting facilitated by experienced and enthused staff all contribute to a unique personal development experience. PEAK veterans have more than just a deserved reputation; they are, the ones who take the initiative, the ones willing to take the lead, willing to share their skills with others.

Title: INTERNATIONAL SERVICE TEAM REGISTRATION 16th World Scout Moot, Portugal 2025.
Description:
https://www.scouts.ie/about-scouting-ireland/international/wsm2025

The World Scout Moot is a world event that brings together Rovers and young leaders from different countries and regions. It promotes inter-cultural exchange, understanding, and friendship. The Moot is designed for young adults with ages between 18 and 25 years old. It takes place every four years and is a unique and enriching experience. The Moot features a wide range of activities and programs, including outdoor adventures, cultural exchanges, community service projects, and educational workshops. These activities are designed to promote personal growth, leadership development, and intercultural learning. The Moot is a significant event in Scouting: it promotes the principles of the World Scout Movement, fosters international cooperation, and provides young adults with a unique and unforgettable experience.
